g.text: Note: (S) in entity title indicates that this entity introduces a one clock cycle delay, (S^2) - two clock cycles etc.
o Screen consists of 16 segments, numbered from 0 to 15
o Each segment is 64 pixels high and 1280 pixels wide
o There are 14 segments for showing trace and 2 segments for settings
o Each segment consists of 4 subsegments
x three subsegments for trace printing - for red, green and blue signals
x one subsegment for time base indication
o Settings segment has one line of text in each subsegment.
So it has 8 lines of text available
o SW3, SW2, SW1, SW0 - time resolution switches
o BTN2 - trigger event choose button
o BTN1 - behaviour after complete reading
Visual Paradigm for UML Standard Edition(Warsaw University)
